The Solidity contract equivalent of the provided decompiled code could look like this:

```solidity
pragma solidity >=0.4.22 <0.9.0;

contract SampleContract {

    function() external payable {
        require(msg.data.length < 4, "Data length is too long");
        require(msg.data.length == 0, "Data length should be zero");
    }
}
```

Please note that the above contract allows any amount of Ether to be sent to it, but it requires the incoming transaction to not contain any data (or contain less than 4 bytes of data, which is contradictory and will lead to a failure in all cases). This is translated from your provided decompiled code. In practice, you would likely want to remove one of the require conditions.
